article.headline: Cornell 69, Ithaca College 67
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Eric Taylor had a game-high 20 points and 10 rebounds to lift Cornell to a 69-67 win over crosstown rival Ithaca Monday night. Cornell, which held a 35-17 rebounding advantage, never trailed in the second half after a 35-35 deadlock at the break. The Big Red (1-3) built a 13-point lead with just over a minute left and staved off a rally by the Bombers (1-1), who scored the final 11 points of the game. Lenny Collins had 15 points and a game-high six assists for Cornell. Khaliq Gant and Ryan Rourke added nine points each. Ithaca shot 52 percent from the floor and had four players in double figures: Jon Whetstone with 15, Ian Houck and Brian Joe with 14, and Jesse Roth with 13. The Bombers broke an early 12-12 tie with an eight-point run, but Cornell responded with a 15-2 run and the teams were tied by the half.
